author: Abhishek Vishnoi
description: US President Donald Trump’s plan to slap a $100,000 fee on H-1B visas is just one more reason to look for outperformance from India’s domestically exposed stocks, which are less vulnerable to the America First agenda.

author: Jennifer Zabasajja
description: South Africa’s trade minister said he was hopeful a trade pact giving many African countries preferential access to the US market will be extended ahead of its expiry later this year.
title: South Africa Says It’s Hopeful US Trade Pact AGOA Will Survive

description: The US president said climate change was “a con job” and denounced green energy in his nearly hour-long address.

description: A Canadian First Nations development organization is recruiting 31 indigenous groups  to propose a new oil pipeline from Alberta to the northern British Columbia coast, a project supported by Alberta’s Premier Danielle Smith and Prime Minister Mark Carney.
title: First Nations Will Seek Ownership of New Oil Sands Pipeline

author: Erik Wasson
description: This is Washington Edition, the newsletter about money, power and politics in the nation’s capital. Today, congressional correspondent Erik Wasson looks at the standoff over government funding. Sign up here and follow us at @bpolitics. Email our editors here.
title: Trump, Democrats Angle to Avoid Blame in Shutdown Fight
